baseline_groups.claim_summary: IDA program participation increases homeownership rates among low-income renters.
baseline_groups.notes: Baseline coefficient 0.011 (p=0.77), NOT significant. All 80 specifications yield insignificant results (0% significant at 5%). The null finding is robust across all specification choices. Point estimates are consistently small and positive (median 0.011, 80% positive).

global_notes: RCT of Individual Development Accounts (IDAs) and homeownership. The American Dream Demonstration experiment, baseline renters followed to Wave 4 (~10 years). The main finding is a ROBUST NULL: no significant treatment effect on homeownership in any of 80 specifications. N=652, so the study may be underpowered to detect small effects. Heterogeneity by income shows marginally significant effect for high-income subgroup (p=0.07).
